title: For Sale/Trade:  1977 S&W Mod 37 No Dash 3" .38
postcontent: For sale is my 1977 made, S&W Mod 37 No Dash 3" .38 revolver. I know I just got it, but I'm not a huge fan of revolvers even though I keep buying them!The Mod 37 was the first "Airweight" revolver, actually before they came out with the name Airweight. The first ones had an aluminum cylinder and frame, but the cylinders would fail due to not being strong enough. They switched back to steel cylinders but kept the aluminum frames. This model IS one of the ones with the steel cylinders, so it's completely safe to fire.This revolver is in amazing condition. I have never fired it, not sure what the previous owner put through it but for it's age...this thing is very nice. The finish is great and it has absolutely 0 rust. There is barely a ring around the cylinder, and it locks up tighter than most new revolvers fresh out of the factory. The revolver comes with a vintage S&W Revolver box (from a different revolver though, not the original box to this one) which is also in pretty good shape!Asking $500 for this. Looking online, the only ones I can find are $500+ in beat up condition, nowhere near the great condition this one is in. I believe $500 is more than fair.Cash is preferred on this one, but I'm open to trade offers...I always like trying new things!Best way to contact me is by texting me at REDACTED or PMing me on here at any time, I always try to reply very quickly..usually within minutes.Thanks for looking!~ Mike
